---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Alert from '../../../components/Alert.astro';
import Tabs from '../../../components/Tabs.tsx';
import Collapsible from '../../../components/Collapsible.tsx';
---
<Layout title="StackTrace Wizard — Setup">
  <h1>StackTrace Wizard — Setup</h1>
  <p>StackTrace Wizard parses, deobfuscates, and visualizes stack traces from any JavaScript or TypeScript runtime.</p>

  <Alert type="info">
    <p>StackTrace Wizard works with V8, SpiderMonkey, and JavaScriptCore runtimes. V8 is auto-detected; other runtimes require a config option.</p>
  </Alert>

  <h2>Installation</h2>
  <Tabs
    client:load
    id="install-stw"
    tabs={[
      { label: 'Yarn', content: '<pre><code>yarn add -D @stacktrace-wizard/core</code></pre>' },
      { label: 'npm', content: '<pre><code>npm install -D @stacktrace-wizard/core</code></pre>' },
    ]}
  />

  <h2>Source Map Configuration</h2>
  <p>For deobfuscation to work, StackTrace Wizard needs access to your source maps. Point it to your build output:</p>
  <pre><code>{`{
  "sourceMaps": {
    "dir": "./dist",
    "include": ["**/*.map"]
  }
}`}</code></pre>

  <h2>CI Integration</h2>
  <p>StackTrace Wizard can run as a post-test step to automatically annotate any failing test output with enriched stack traces. Add the reporter to your test runner config:</p>

  <Tabs
    client:load
    id="ci-runner"
    tabs={[
      { label: 'Vitest', content: '<pre><code>// vitest.config.ts\nreporters: [\'default\', \'@stacktrace-wizard/vitest-reporter\']</code></pre>' },
      { label: 'Jest', content: '<pre><code>// jest.config.js\nreporters: [\'default\', \'@stacktrace-wizard/jest-reporter\']</code></pre>' },
    ]}
  />

  <h2>Web Dashboard</h2>
  <p>Start the local dashboard to paste and analyze stack traces interactively:</p>
  <pre><code>npx stacktrace-wizard serve</code></pre>
  <p>The dashboard opens at <code>http://localhost:9800</code> and provides a searchable history of every trace you've analyzed.</p>

  <p>Dashboard capabilities:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Paste raw stack traces for instant deobfuscation</li>
    <li>Searchable history of all analyzed traces</li>
    <li>Side-by-side comparison of obfuscated and deobfuscated output</li>
    <li>Link sharing for individual traces</li>
  </ul>

  <Collapsible client:load title="Dashboard keyboard shortcuts" data-testid="dashboard-shortcuts">
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Ctrl+V</strong> — Paste and analyze a new trace</li>
      <li><strong>Ctrl+K</strong> — Open the trace search</li>
      <li><strong>J / K</strong> — Navigate between frames in a trace</li>
      <li><strong>Enter</strong> — Open the source file for the selected frame</li>
      <li><strong>Esc</strong> — Close the current panel</li>
    </ul>
  </Collapsible>
</Layout>
